      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 57: `makeGitObjectUnreachable()` silently ignores errors from `remove_all(packDir, ec)` and returns `false` for both expected packed-object fallback and actual filesystem failures. That makes future tests hard to diagnose and can leave partially corrupted state behind. Return an explicit status/error or assert that fallback removal succeeded in callers that intentionally use it. Suggested fix: ```suggestion\nif (std::filesystem::is_directory(packDir, ec)) {\n    ec.clear();\n    std::filesystem::remove_all(packDir, ec);\n    CPPUNIT_ASSERT_MESSAGE(ec.message(), !ec);\n}\nreturn false;\n```",
